@maggot: ive got some advice: hes obviously taken the screenshots from vlc, and ive experienced it, vlc ruins the video quality, for example ive taken the same screenshot using wmp and u can see the difference: 
bozx's screen:http://www.imagebam.com/image/18be29150807922
my screen of the same rip: http://www.imagebam.com/image/5e41cc150827268

@SD_rocks

I hate to be the bearer of bad news but guys who know their stuff think 8475Kbps IS a low bit rate. Absolute minimum for 1080 resolution of a live-action film should be > 9000Kbps. 10k and above is preferable.

Your screenshots are the EXACT same quality as BOZX. The only difference is the processing: your screenshot is much higher contrast. The human eye prefers contrast, and the darker blacks mask the macroblocking better - but it is only creating the illusion of looking "better". Increase the brightness of your monitor you'll see the macroblocking is still there. Someone with a trained eye won't even have to do that, it's obvious there is no increase in resolution or quality between the two screenshots.

@SD_rocks 
It's my opinion that the original does look better just because when increasing contrast, you run the risk of blending the darkest colors together, as well as the brights- the other colors are "stretched to fit" in an attempt to make other things in the mid range more visible. This new shot does just that -just a little too heavy with the contrast. 

Of course, with that being said, it does look prettier if you aren't focusing on the brights or the darks, even if its just got higher contrast put on it.

